It's not the end of the world.

01:08.529 --> 01:12.065
It is! It absolutely is!

01:12.099 --> 01:14.567
So stop trying to cheer me up!

01:14.601 --> 01:16.452
Did something happen at Armani?

01:16.487 --> 01:18.655
She couldn't fit into
the dress she wanted.

01:18.706 --> 01:21.407
And then the salesgirl
called me fat.

01:21.441 --> 01:23.609
She said you were a size 2.

01:23.627 --> 01:25.044
It's the same thing!

01:25.079 --> 01:26.946
She used to be a size zero.

01:26.964 --> 01:30.166
But years of Mexican cooking
have disfigured me.

01:30.217 --> 01:32.118
If you insult my cooking
one more time,

01:32.136 --> 01:35.121
you'll know what it means
to be disfigured by a Mexican.

01:36.590 --> 01:39.425
Um, can I, um, talk to you guys
about something?

01:39.459 --> 01:41.127
Not now, dear.

01:41.145 --> 01:44.063
I'm going upstairs and take
some aspirin and lay down.

01:44.098 --> 01:47.317
After I've gotten up and purged
the aspirin, we can chat.

01:47.351 --> 01:49.269
But this can't wait.

01:49.303 --> 01:52.021
There's a problem
with the gardeners.

01:52.072 --> 01:53.823
What sort of problem?

01:53.857 --> 01:55.908
They're refusing to work
until they get paid.

01:57.411 --> 01:59.329
I wrote them a check on Monday.

01:59.363 --> 02:00.980
It bounced.

02:00.998 --> 02:02.332
Bounced?

02:02.366 --> 02:04.417
And I just got a call
from our pool guy.

02:04.451 --> 02:06.536
His check bounced, too.

02:06.587 --> 02:10.156
Mrs. Delatour, I think we better
call your business manager.

02:16.880 --> 02:19.515
I'm calling
for Genevieve Delatour.

02:19.550 --> 02:22.302
She needs to speak
with Myron Moyer immediately.

02:22.336 --> 02:24.670
There seems to be some problem
with her account.

02:24.688 --> 02:26.389
There's no need to worry,
darling.

02:26.440 --> 02:29.142
Myron's been taking care
of my money for years.

02:29.176 --> 02:31.227
He'll figure this out.

02:31.278 --> 02:33.346
What do you mean
you can't find him?

02:35.049 --> 02:37.016
Oh, my God.

02:37.034 --> 02:38.985
"Oh, my God"?

02:39.019 --> 02:41.154
Why are you saying
"Oh, my God"?

02:41.188 --> 02:44.407
Yes. Um...

02:44.458 --> 02:45.992
I'll tell her.

02:47.411 --> 02:49.412
Zoila, what?
What's happening?

02:51.832 --> 02:53.466
Your business manager
has disappeared

02:53.500 --> 02:55.385
and taken all of your money
with him.

02:55.419 --> 02:57.587
Honey, I'm sorry,

02:57.638 --> 02:59.972
but because you gave Myron
control over everything,

03:00.007 --> 03:02.558
you now don't have a cent
to your name.

03:06.647 --> 03:09.215
Mrs. Delatour?

03:10.484 --> 03:13.552
Then I was right.

03:13.570 --> 03:16.055
It is the end of the world.

