Hello?

03:37.761 --> 03:39.295
Aah!

03:39.346 --> 03:41.464
You shouldn't sneak up
on people like that.

03:41.515 --> 03:42.765
It's very, very rude.

03:42.800 --> 03:46.636
You know what else
is rude?

03:46.687 --> 03:48.604
Breaking into people's homes.

03:48.639 --> 03:49.772
Excuse me.

03:49.807 --> 03:51.757
I knocked,

03:51.775 --> 03:54.360
and that cute black guy said
I could borrow some eggs.

03:54.395 --> 03:56.429
But... you don't have any.

03:56.447 --> 03:57.763
That's because
the sexy brown girl

03:57.781 --> 03:59.598
hasn't gone to the store yet.

03:59.616 --> 04:01.100
Who are you?

04:01.118 --> 04:03.486
I'm Julie. I work next door,
for the Higgins.

04:03.537 --> 04:05.604
Oh. Right.

04:05.622 --> 04:07.490
I heard they hired a cook.

04:07.541 --> 04:10.376
Actually, I'm a chef.

04:10.411 --> 04:11.627
What's the difference?

04:11.662 --> 04:14.547
$60,000 in tuition.

04:14.581 --> 04:16.582
And a hat.

04:16.616 --> 04:20.168
I studied at the Cordon Bleu
in Paris.

04:20.220 --> 04:21.387
Fancy.

04:21.422 --> 04:23.789
So where am I gonna get
some eggs?

04:23.807 --> 04:27.260
Did the Cordon Bleu not teach
you about supermarkets?

04:27.294 --> 04:29.295
You're funny.

04:29.313 --> 04:30.513
Sort of.

04:30.564 --> 04:34.233
Uh, the problem is,
I don't have a car.

04:34.268 --> 04:35.234
Do you have a car?

04:35.269 --> 04:37.136
Why?

04:37.154 --> 04:39.405
I was thinking
you could drive me.

04:39.440 --> 04:41.441
Ah!

04:41.475 --> 04:42.742
Now you're funny.

04:42.776 --> 04:44.160
Sort of.

04:44.194 --> 04:46.412
Hey, Carmen.
I see you've met Julie.

04:46.447 --> 04:50.533
Yes. Yes. I was just saying,
"Welcome to the neighborhood."

04:50.584 --> 04:51.817
And good-bye.

04:51.835 --> 04:53.286
I'm not new
to the neighborhood.

04:53.320 --> 04:56.322
I-I used to work for
Barbara Crump over on Canon,

04:56.340 --> 04:58.124
but I had to quit.

04:58.158 --> 05:00.176
She got got a rottweiler,
and I'm allergic to dogs.

05:00.210 --> 05:02.595
And I told her
she would have to choose.

05:02.629 --> 05:05.598
Can you believe she chose
a rottweiler over me?

05:07.167 --> 05:09.385
Don't let me answer that.

05:09.436 --> 05:12.688
So, uh, Julie,
uh, do we have any eggs?

05:12.723 --> 05:14.340
No.

05:14.358 --> 05:16.609
Somebody forgot to go
to the store.

05:16.643 --> 05:18.861
Well...

05:18.896 --> 05:20.396
How about I run you over there
myself?

05:20.447 --> 05:23.950
Ah! Thank you so much.
You are so sweet.

05:23.984 --> 05:26.319
Uh, I'm gonna just run next door
and grab my wallet.

05:26.353 --> 05:29.205
Okay?

05:30.690 --> 05:32.625
So...
What do you think?

05:32.659 --> 05:34.193
- Of what?
- Of Julie.

05:34.211 --> 05:35.294
She's cute, right?

05:35.329 --> 05:38.331
I think I'm gonna ask her out.

05:50.844 --> 05:52.228
Oh, God.

05:52.262 --> 05:54.380
Don't say that.

05:54.398 --> 05:55.765
What?

05:55.816 --> 05:59.151
You took the lord's name
in vain. It's not right.

05:59.186 --> 06:01.270
What should I say?

06:01.321 --> 06:03.439
You can say...

06:03.490 --> 06:05.107
"Goodness"!

06:05.158 --> 06:07.726
After what we just did...

06:07.744 --> 06:09.111
I know.

06:09.162 --> 06:11.364
...that doesn't seem right either.

06:11.398 --> 06:13.366
But it was good, wasn't it?

06:13.400 --> 06:14.900
Ohh, it was great.

06:14.918 --> 06:17.537
What about you?

06:17.571 --> 06:19.789
How do you feel?

06:19.840 --> 06:22.675
I'm...

06:22.709 --> 06:24.594
happy.

06:24.628 --> 06:28.914
You sound surprised.

06:28.932 --> 06:31.934
After Ernesto died,
I was so sad.

06:31.969 --> 06:36.522
Then I had to leave my son
to come here.

06:36.557 --> 06:39.609
I cried every night.

06:39.643 --> 06:42.695
After a while,
I started to think,

06:42.729 --> 06:47.066
if I wasn't crying,
I was happy,

06:47.100 --> 06:49.935
'cause I forgot what
real happiness feels like.

06:49.953 --> 06:53.105
I'm happy, too.

06:55.292 --> 06:58.878
Mmm, what are you doing?

06:58.912 --> 07:00.830
Come on, Rosie.

07:00.881 --> 07:02.381
Just a little more happiness.

07:02.416 --> 07:05.334
But I got dishes to wash

07:05.385 --> 07:06.836
and floors to mop.

07:06.887 --> 07:08.921
And...

07:08.955 --> 07:12.058
Oh, God!

07:14.461 --> 07:16.729
The good news is
we've found Myron.

07:16.763 --> 07:17.847
Oh, thank God.

07:17.898 --> 07:20.766
The bad news is he's in Brunei.

07:20.800 --> 07:22.351
Why is that bad?

07:22.402 --> 07:24.153
We don't have an extradition
treaty with Brunei.

07:24.187 --> 07:26.405
So the police can't arrest him?

07:26.440 --> 07:30.776
No. No, Myron Moyer can spend
every cent of Genevieve's money,

07:30.810 --> 07:32.745
and no one can touch him.

07:32.779 --> 07:34.246
Well, what can we do?

07:40.337 --> 07:42.655
Hey there, Genevieve.
Can I talk to you for a minute?

07:42.673 --> 07:44.507
Of course, Michael.

07:44.541 --> 07:46.592
You look very dashing today.

07:46.627 --> 07:47.960
Thanks.

07:47.994 --> 07:50.296
Um, m-my law firm
is working with Interpol

07:50.330 --> 07:52.098
to try and get your money back.

07:52.132 --> 07:54.800
But...
it doesn't look good.

07:54.834 --> 07:58.671
Um... And we think you may want
to sell this house.

07:58.689 --> 08:01.440
But where would
Remi and I live?

08:01.475 --> 08:04.343
Fancy apartment?
A nice condo?

08:04.361 --> 08:05.778
- "Minium"?
- Mm.

08:05.812 --> 08:06.896
No.

08:06.947 --> 08:10.015
I like it here.

08:10.033 --> 08:12.785
But you can't afford
the mortgage now.

08:12.819 --> 08:14.654
This is America.

08:14.688 --> 08:17.206
We have safety nets.

08:17.240 --> 08:19.542
Surely there must be
some entitlement program

08:19.576 --> 08:22.294
that will help me pay
for my mansion.

08:22.329 --> 08:23.713
Well, you'd think so,

08:23.747 --> 08:26.749
but most government aid
only goes to poor people.

08:26.800 --> 08:28.551
That's not fair.

08:28.585 --> 08:31.387
They don't have the same
expenses rich people do.

08:31.421 --> 08:34.539
That's why people choose
to be poor in the first place.

08:34.558 --> 08:36.558
There's no overhead.

08:38.345 --> 08:39.595
Mom, where are you going?

08:41.014 --> 08:43.381
This man has given me stress,

08:43.400 --> 08:44.817
so I'm going to the spa

08:44.851 --> 08:47.570
to have Hans beat me with reeds
until it goes away.

08:47.604 --> 08:49.021
That's my point, Genevieve.

08:49.055 --> 08:51.941
You can no longer afford
the spa.

08:51.992 --> 08:55.361
You can't even afford the reeds.

08:55.395 --> 08:59.749
Hopefully, my relationship
with Hans is strong enough

08:59.783 --> 09:03.335
that he'll agree
to beat me for free.

09:04.871 --> 09:07.790
Why don't I just give her some
of the money from my trust fund?

09:07.841 --> 09:08.958
That should cheer her up.

09:09.009 --> 09:10.459
Actually,

09:10.510 --> 09:12.428
about your trust fund...

09:13.747 --> 09:16.098
It's gone, too?

09:18.418 --> 09:21.920
I'm so sorry, Remi.

09:45.462 --> 09:50.466
Ida, it's Marisol.
Did you get my message?

09:50.500 --> 09:53.052
I did. You said Eddie
remembered something.

09:53.086 --> 09:57.973
Yes. He once heard Flora
talking about a DVD.

09:58.008 --> 10:00.059
What kind of DVD?

10:00.093 --> 10:04.630
I'm not sure, but she was
using it to blackmail somebody.

10:04.648 --> 10:06.732
Where do you think she kept it?

10:06.767 --> 10:10.803
It's got to be somewhere
in the Powell house.

10:10.821 --> 10:12.521
It's got to be.

10:38.849 --> 10:40.833
Marisol?

10:44.771 --> 10:46.438
Have you seen my Birkin bag?

10:46.473 --> 10:48.941
It's right over there.

10:50.527 --> 10:52.728
I'm meeting my friend Genevieve
at the spa.

10:52.779 --> 10:55.531
The poor thing is having
horrible financial troubles,

10:55.565 --> 10:59.184
and I want to make sure
that she knows that I am not.

11:00.987 --> 11:02.955
Is everything okay?

11:02.989 --> 11:05.040
Everything's fine.

11:05.075 --> 11:07.076
I'm gonna go finish my ironing.

11:29.616 --> 11:32.300
Rosie!

11:32.335 --> 11:33.785
What's wrong?

11:33.803 --> 11:35.587
My silk top isn't here.

11:35.621 --> 11:37.839
That's because I didn't pick up
the dry cleaning yet.

11:37.890 --> 11:40.592
I have to look spectacular
today.

11:40.626 --> 11:42.310
Billy Bush is interviewing me,

11:42.345 --> 11:44.679
and the last thing I wanna do
is give that bitch ammo.

11:44.730 --> 11:46.964
I'm sorry.
I got a late start.

11:46.982 --> 11:49.484
Why do I have
so much Donna Karan?

11:49.518 --> 11:51.486
How many funerals can I go to?

11:51.520 --> 11:53.738
This one's nice.

11:53.773 --> 11:55.824
Whatever. Help me get ready.

11:57.777 --> 11:59.160
You know, Rosie,

11:59.195 --> 12:01.196
the house
has been a mess lately.

12:01.247 --> 12:03.415
I'm starting to think
you don't like your job.

12:03.449 --> 12:06.868
No, no. I like it very much.

12:06.919 --> 12:08.670
You should.

12:08.704 --> 12:10.839
You don't have to work
for boring people.

12:10.873 --> 12:12.507
Spence and I are celebrities.

12:12.541 --> 12:15.844
Yes.
My job is very exciting.

12:15.878 --> 12:17.712
So let's step it up a notch.

12:17.763 --> 12:20.515
No more dirty dishes
in the sink.

12:20.549 --> 12:21.850
No more dust on the shelves.

12:21.884 --> 12:24.719
I'll do better. I promise.

12:24.770 --> 12:25.854
I hope so.

12:25.888 --> 12:27.522
From what I can see,

12:27.556 --> 12:30.508
all you've done all morning
is wash my sheets.

12:41.404 --> 12:42.687
Hi.

12:42.705 --> 12:44.689
Brought you a little treat
to cheer you up.

12:44.707 --> 12:46.324
Cheer me up?

12:46.358 --> 12:49.861
No, I'm good. I'm good.
I'm... I'm great, actually.

12:49.879 --> 12:51.996
Really? 'Cause with everything
that's going on

12:52.030 --> 12:53.798
with your mom and the money...

12:53.833 --> 12:55.333
I know, right?

12:55.367 --> 12:57.001
I mean, usually you hear
your trust fund's gone,

12:57.035 --> 12:58.369
your freak out, but I'm thinking
this could be the best thing

12:58.387 --> 12:59.871
that's ever happened
to this family.

12:59.889 --> 13:01.339
Really?
Yeah!

13:01.373 --> 13:02.841
I mean, we'll move
into a smaller house,

13:02.875 --> 13:04.342
where we can talk and hang out

13:04.376 --> 13:06.895
and... and really connect,
you know?

13:06.929 --> 13:09.564
Maybe we'll move into a tent.
Have you ever been camping?

13:09.598 --> 13:11.549
Uh... no.

13:11.567 --> 13:12.767
Shut up!

13:12.818 --> 13:15.103
We are going camping.

13:15.154 --> 13:17.555
You're... taking this
really well.

13:17.573 --> 13:18.890
Well, there's no other way
to take it, girl.

13:18.908 --> 13:20.358
There's no other way to be.

13:20.392 --> 13:22.160
Okay, well,
I just wanted you to know

13:22.194 --> 13:23.828
that I'm here if you need
to talk or anything.

13:23.863 --> 13:25.830
I so appreciate that.

13:25.865 --> 13:27.499
But like I said,
I'm... I'm good.

13:27.533 --> 13:30.618
I'm really, really excellent.

13:40.429 --> 13:43.715
Marisol had
a nasty little shock today.

13:43.749 --> 13:45.517
Did she?

13:45.551 --> 13:50.421
I believe she happened upon
one of your nauseating DVDs.

13:50.439 --> 13:52.440
Which one?

13:52.475 --> 13:56.895
This exercise in voyeurism
featured the Stappords.

13:56.929 --> 13:58.596
Did Marisol say anything?

13:58.614 --> 14:00.031
Mnh-mnh.

14:00.065 --> 14:00.932
But she was hiding it
when I walked in the room.

14:00.950 --> 14:02.817
She was clearly mortified.

14:02.868 --> 14:05.770
Maybe.

14:05.788 --> 14:09.073
Maybe not.

14:09.107 --> 14:11.960
Marisol has an agenda.
We've known this for a while.

14:13.379 --> 14:14.879
Maybe she was searching for it.

14:14.914 --> 14:16.631
Why would she do that?

14:16.665 --> 14:19.384
So she could use it against me.

14:19.418 --> 14:21.836
I think it's time
to fire Marisol.

14:21.887 --> 14:23.972
I also have an agenda, Adrian.

14:24.006 --> 14:25.890
Mine is to not do housework.

14:25.925 --> 14:27.892
We can hire someone else.

14:27.927 --> 14:29.060
I finally have a maid

14:29.094 --> 14:30.478
who can cook
and conjugate English verbs.

14:30.513 --> 14:32.480
If you think I'm letting her go,
you're crazy.

14:32.515 --> 14:33.965
She wanders around this house
without any supervision.

14:33.983 --> 14:36.901
What happens if she stumbles
onto my collection?

14:36.936 --> 14:38.636
Well...

14:38.654 --> 14:40.522
First, she'll wanna
wash her hands.

14:40.573 --> 14:41.906
Pay attention, darling.

14:41.941 --> 14:43.525
If she finds those DVDs,

14:43.576 --> 14:46.578
she will tell people,
and we will be humiliated.

14:46.612 --> 14:47.862
For God sake, Adrian.

14:47.913 --> 14:49.581
The woman cleans tile grout
for a living.

14:49.615 --> 14:50.999
If you can't shield this secret
from her,

14:51.033 --> 14:53.651
you're not the brilliant
degenerate I married.

14:55.454 --> 14:59.657
Evelyn, that was precisely
the pep talk I needed.

15:22.698 --> 15:24.148
Am I interrupting something?

15:24.182 --> 15:25.900
Yeah.

15:25.951 --> 15:28.653
Okay, just as a reminder,
my room is right below yours.

15:28.687 --> 15:31.573
Sorry, I didn't... realize
we were that loud.

15:31.624 --> 15:32.574
"We"?

15:32.625 --> 15:34.158
Uh, Julie, say "hi" to Carmen.

15:34.192 --> 15:38.046
Hey, Carmen.
Don't come in. I'm super naked.

15:38.080 --> 15:39.964
Isn't this your first date?

15:39.999 --> 15:42.083
And if it keeps going this well,
we'll definitely have a second.

15:42.134 --> 15:43.534
Good night.

15:43.552 --> 15:45.536
Stop. You can't do this.

15:45.554 --> 15:47.005
Do what?

15:47.039 --> 15:48.640
Have sex with that woman.

15:48.674 --> 15:50.258
She's not up to your standards.

15:50.309 --> 15:52.209
Wait.

15:53.879 --> 15:55.013
What are my standards?

15:55.047 --> 15:57.815
I am your standards.

15:57.850 --> 16:00.217
But you don't want to date me.

16:00.235 --> 16:02.186
Well, just because
you can't have filet mignon

16:02.220 --> 16:04.656
doesn't mean that you have to
settle for fast food.

16:04.690 --> 16:07.075
For your information,
Julie is not a compromise.

16:07.109 --> 16:09.110
She's a smart, elegant woman.

16:09.161 --> 16:12.730
Sam!
My breasts are getting cold.

16:12.748 --> 16:13.998
I have to go.

16:14.033 --> 16:15.450
No! You need to stop.

16:15.501 --> 16:17.201
What do you care
who I sleep with?

16:17.235 --> 16:19.737
Well, I...

16:19.755 --> 16:20.705
I don't.

16:20.739 --> 16:22.790
Good.

16:29.765 --> 16:30.848
What's this?

16:30.883 --> 16:32.383
The ring you gave me
ten years ago.

16:32.417 --> 16:34.251
I want you to sell it.
You need the money.

16:34.269 --> 16:36.220
Zoila, it was a gift.

16:36.254 --> 16:39.090
I told you at the time
it was way too extravagant.

16:39.108 --> 16:41.059
You said hang onto it
in case of a rainy day.

16:41.093 --> 16:44.529
Well, it turns out it's
your roof that's leaking.

16:46.699 --> 16:48.866
Did I ever tell you
how I got this?

16:48.901 --> 16:51.119
It was an apology
from my second husband.

16:51.153 --> 16:53.154
- Philippe?
- Yes.

16:53.205 --> 16:55.873
I caught him sleeping
with my nutritionist.

16:55.908 --> 16:57.158
He was so ashamed,

16:57.209 --> 16:59.077
he showed up the next morning
with this ring.

16:59.111 --> 17:02.780
I screamed, "You can't buy
my forgiveness with diamonds."

17:02.798 --> 17:04.281
Then I threw it at him.

17:04.299 --> 17:06.851
The big stone scratched
his cornea.

17:06.885 --> 17:09.053
So it has sentimental value.

17:09.088 --> 17:11.689
Oh, Zoila,
I love you for offering,

17:11.723 --> 17:13.156
but I can't take this.

17:13.192 --> 17:15.259
You can't afford
to be generous either.

17:15.294 --> 17:18.179
You're broke. Remember?

17:18.230 --> 17:21.983
All this talk about money
is giving me a migraine.

17:22.017 --> 17:24.318
Can't we talk about this
next week?

17:24.353 --> 17:26.904
I won't be here next week,
sweetie.

17:26.939 --> 17:28.156
What?!

17:28.190 --> 17:29.857
You can't afford to pay me,

17:29.908 --> 17:32.076
and I can't afford
not to get paid.

17:32.111 --> 17:34.328
