all your money, would it?

21:57.607 --> 21:59.357
So you've heard.

22:00.509 --> 22:03.195
Well, it's true.

22:03.229 --> 22:05.147
I am broke,

22:05.181 --> 22:06.531
and I need your help.

22:06.566 --> 22:09.734
But it is also true

22:09.786 --> 22:12.654
that I want you back
in my life.

22:12.688 --> 22:14.623
I've missed you, my love.

22:14.657 --> 22:17.358
I'm so glad to hear that.

22:22.632 --> 22:24.583
Do you remember this manet?

22:24.634 --> 22:26.635
Of course.

22:26.669 --> 22:28.703
You bought it on our honeymoon.

22:28.721 --> 22:32.674
It was recently appraised
at a million dollars.

22:32.708 --> 22:34.509
Would you like it?

22:34.543 --> 22:37.212
Oh, Philippe.

22:37.230 --> 22:40.381
You would just give it to me?
No strings attached?

22:40.399 --> 22:41.850
Well...

22:41.884 --> 22:44.486
I didn't say that.

22:49.325 --> 22:51.526
How'd it go?

22:51.560 --> 22:54.529
He offered me a painting
worth a million dollars.

22:54.563 --> 22:56.531
That's great!

22:56.565 --> 22:57.749
What's wrong?

22:57.783 --> 23:00.368
He offered it on the condition

23:00.402 --> 23:02.403
that I sleep with him.

23:02.421 --> 23:04.906
What?

23:04.924 --> 23:08.677
He said I was
the best he'd ever had,

23:08.711 --> 23:10.762
and it was worth
that much money for...

23:10.796 --> 23:14.799
and these are his words...

23:14.851 --> 23:18.386
another ride
on the sensual merry-go-round

23:18.420 --> 23:20.188
that is my body.

23:21.524 --> 23:24.392
So did you give him a ride?

23:24.426 --> 23:26.194
No!

23:26.229 --> 23:28.530
How can you even ask that?

23:28.564 --> 23:30.482
You're broke!

23:30.533 --> 23:32.317
I may be destitute,

23:32.368 --> 23:35.871
but I would never debase myself
just to pay a few bills.

23:35.905 --> 23:38.490
I'm sorry.

23:38.541 --> 23:40.108
I'm also very proud of you.

23:41.460 --> 23:44.663
Thank you.

23:44.714 --> 23:46.631
So...

23:46.666 --> 23:48.283
What happens now?

23:48.301 --> 23:52.287
You are going to learn
to take care of yourself.

23:52.305 --> 23:53.388
I am?

23:53.422 --> 23:55.590
And this is a good thing.

23:55.624 --> 23:57.425
It's your chance
to finally prove to people

23:57.459 --> 24:00.762
that you're more than a shallow,
spoiled Beverly Hills diva.

24:00.796 --> 24:03.231
I'm sure you can get a job

24:03.266 --> 24:04.983
selling clothes
at a fancy shop,

24:05.017 --> 24:07.686
or hostessing
at an upscale bistro.

24:07.737 --> 24:10.822
I can teach you how
to cook your own meals

24:10.856 --> 24:13.325
and wash your own clothes.

24:13.359 --> 24:15.827
And even though you'll fall
asleep exhausted every night,

24:15.861 --> 24:18.196
you will be happy
because you'll know

24:18.247 --> 24:21.249
you are finally
a productive member of society.

24:21.284 --> 24:22.500
And what are you doing?

24:22.535 --> 24:25.253
I'm starting up
the merry-go-round.

24:26.622 --> 24:28.373
But, honey...

24:28.424 --> 24:30.759
Relax. It's Philippe.

24:30.793 --> 24:32.928
And if memory serves me,

24:32.962 --> 24:35.347
